        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 4:50AM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 450 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Upper Buffalo Wilderness Area, or 14 miles southwest of Jasper,
moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mossville...                      Boxley...
Wayton...                         Compton...
Lost Valley State Park...         Low Gap...
Crossroad...                      Vendor...
Swain...                          Parthenon...
Gum Springs in Newton County...   Piercetown...
Mt Judea...                       Carver...
Erbie...                          Upper Buffalo Wilderness Area...
Nail...                           Jasper...
Pruitt...                         Ponca...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
